	First name	Town name

	Object name

¬ß1 The landlord rent ....... rooms for housing to the tenant. Housing area amounts to........ m2 
 
¬ß2 Alternative 1: Leased from ............................................ onwards. 
Lease expires at the month-end that occurs ‚Ä¶....... full months after notice.
 
Alternative 2: Leased from ............................................ to ........................................... with ...... months 
notice. Unless notice is given, the lease expires at the above stated date. The tenant must vacate
without reminder. (This option can only be used for rental period of up to 9 months). 
 
¬ß3 The rent is ................ SEK per month. The rent is paid one month in advance.
 
¬ß4 The rent includes: (  )Electricity,   (  )Heat,   (  )Stairwell cleaning,   (  )Garage,   (  )Telephone,   (  )Private toilet,   
(  )Separate kitchen/kitchenette,   (  ) Internet  
The housing area is: (  )Furnished,   (  )Unfurnished  
Rent includes access to: (  )Kitchen,   (  )Washing machine,    (  )Toilet/shower,    (  )Common area  
 
¬ß5 The landlord is responsible for the proper operation of vital equipment, such as electricity switches, washing machine, pickings‚Äô in faucets and so on, in accordance with agreements between the landlord and the property owner. In cases where the landlord is the property owner, he is solely responsible.
 
¬ß6 The tenant may not, without the landlord's written consent, carry out painting, wallpapering or any comparable measure.
 
¬ß7 The rental includes furniture according to the attached list of inventory. The tenant acknowledges the inventory by signing the list of inventory. After the lease expires, the landlord signs the tenants copy of the list of inventory or otherwise acknowledges restoration of the inventory. The tenant is responsible for damage or loss of inventory.
 
¬ß8 The tenant is responsible for arranging a separate home insurance for their belongings.
 
¬ß9 The tenant must take good care of the rented property. Should damage occur, the tenant is responsible therefore, unless he can demonstrate that he is not responsible for causing the damage.
 
¬ß10 The tenant shall not, without permission, make available or rent out all or part of residential space.
 
¬ß11 The landlord must obtain permit to rent out the property from the property owner.
 
¬ß12 The tenant commits to respect the code of conduct the landlord has to comply in relation to the property owner. 
 
¬ß13 Special regulations ....................................................................................................................................................... 
 
¬ß14 This lease has been drawn up in two separate copies, of which the landlord and the tenant has taken one each.
 
By signature the tenant acknowledge he has received ....... keys to the accommodation.

contracts.name: enUS-sublet-contract-2
contracts.contents:
SUBLEASE AGREEMENT FOR A RESIDENTIAL APARTMENT
Information
Landlord (The holder of the master lease)
Tenant (The person/persons to sublease the apartment)
Apartment to be sublet
Rent
Electricity Heating
Internet connection
Gauge reading
Garage and parking space

Subletting an apartment means that the holder of the master lease lets his/her apartment to another person for independent use. To sublet an apartment always requires prior permission constitutes grounds for termination of the master lease. If the landlord charge a rent which is higher than the rent paid by the landlord the Swedish rent tribunal can rule that any excess rent for the past two years must be paid back. If the apartment is furnished a ten percent increase on the monthly rent it is seen as reasonable.

Name
